<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The supervision of stock market trading in Japan is to be tightened by the 
appointment of a team within the Ministry of Finance that will examine 
allegations of insider trading and stock manipulation . . . Avery International 
of Pasadena said it settled a patent infringement suit with Minnesota Mining 
&amp; Manufacturing over a material used to attach disposable diaper tapes. 
Under the settlement, 3M agreed to pay Avery $15 million and future royalties 
over the next three years. 
</P>
