<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Home Box Office reportedly will enter advertiser-supported cable service with a 
new 24-hour all-comedy channel. HBO, which for now is declining comment on the 
venture, has scheduled a Tuesday news conference in New York where plans for 
the new channel are expected to be announced. The most recent 
advertiser-supported cable TV venture was Ted Turner's TNT channel, which 
started up last October. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
