<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
BRUCKNER, CHAMINADE HAMMER MONTEBELLO IN 3-A WILD-CARD MATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior Chris Bruckner, soon to be spiking the ball for UCLA, had a match-high 
26 kills Wednesday night as Chaminade High swept Montebello, 15-2, 15-10, 
15-11, in a Southern Section 3-A Division wild-card playoff at Chaminade. 
</P>
<P>
Bruckner (6-foot-5, 190 pounds), a three-year starter who is averaging 26.5 
kills and seven blocks this season, committed to UCLA earlier this year and 
said he will sign a letter of intent today. 
</P>
<P>
"You can't beat UCLA volleyball," Bruckner said of the Bruins, who have won 13 
national championships since 1970. "It's No. 1." 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade (13-6), which finished second in the San Fernando Valley League, fell 
behind, 2-0, in the first game before Steve Gerevas scored seven consecutive 
points. Marc Miles then served eight consecutive points to close out the game. 
</P>
<P>
Tim Hayes had 12 kills and Fran Reyes added nine. Chaminade, seeded 12th, plays 
fourth-seeded Brentwood in a first-round match Friday at Brentwood. 
</P>
<P>
In other wild-card matches: 
</P>
<P>
San Marcos d. Crespi, 8-15, 13-15, 16-14, 15-9, 15-6 -- The Celts were a point 
away from sweeping the 4-A Division wild-card match, but visiting San Marcos 
rallied in each of the final three games. 
</P>
<P>
Crespi (12-5) led, 14-13, in the third game after rallying in each of the first 
two games. San Marcos led, 5-1 and 7-2, before the Celts staged comebacks. 
</P>
<P>
Crespi led in each of the final two games, 7-3 and 6-3, but San Marcos rallied, 
scoring the final 12 points of the deciding game. 
</P>
<P>
Ken Lynch led Crespi with 24 kills. Chris McGee added 17 and Brian Scully had 
12. 
</P>
<P>
Glendale d. Lynwood, 15-9, 15-5, 15-6 -- Glendale, which finished third in the 
Central League, coasted in a 3-A match at Lynwood. The third-seeded Dynamiters 
(12-5) will play at unseeded Bishop Montgomery on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Dos Pueblos d. St. Francis, 15-5, 15-2, 15-13 -- The Golden Knights (10-9), who 
finished third in the Del Rey League, were eliminated in a 4-A match at Dos 
Pueblos. 
</P>
<P>
CITY SECTION SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Carson 15, Chatsworth 6 -- Laura Roopenian (12-4) was shelled for 17 hits in a 
4-A Division first-round game at Chatsworth. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly Tubin hit a two-run home run in the first and Mara Phillips hit a solo 
shot in the seventh in a losing effort. Roopenian added a single and a triple. 
Chatsworth (12-4) committed nine errors. 
</P>
<P>
In other first-round games: 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills 5, Birmingham 1 -- The Highlanders collected nine hits and 
capitalized on six Birmingham errors in a 4-A Division game at Birmingham. 
</P>
<P>
Banning 10, Canoga Park 0 -- Kricket Kearn lost her no-hitter on Belen Mota's 
two-put single in the seventh inning, but the fifth-seeded Pilots breezed by 
the 12th-seeded Hunters in a 4-A Division game at Banning. 
</P>
<P>
Poly 25, Dorsey 8 -- Junior Jodi Soto pitched a six-hitter with 12 strikeouts 
and added a double at Poly as the top-seeded Parrots (17-2) won their 15th in a 
row in a 3-A Division game. 
</P>
<P>
Julie Dawson was three for four, including a home run, with six RBIs. 
</P>
