<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two pedestrians were killed Wednesday when they were struck by the driver of a 
pickup truck who lost control while exiting Interstate 5 onto Pershing Drive, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Dead at the scene were James Lawton Cook Jr., 36, of San Diego, and Albert 
Nolan Badon, 41, of Santa Ana, a deputy coroner said. 
</P>
<P>
Both men were walking along Pershing Drive just after 1:30 a.m. when the 
truck's driver, Melvin C. Jones, left the northbound I-5 off-ramp onto 
eastbound Pershing, swerved and hit them, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Jones' truck then crossed the center divider and westbound lanes of Pershing 
Drive before hitting an embankment, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jones, 37, was taken to UC San Diego Medical Center, where he was treated and 
released, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the district attorney's office is reviewing the case. 
</P>
