<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: W. LOS ANGELES; 
</P>
<P>
FEINSTEIN TO SPEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former San Francisco Mayor Dianne Feinstein, a possible Democratic candidate 
for governor, will address the 44th Assembly District Council tonight. 
Feinstein will appear at the group's 7:30 p.m. meeting at 10868 W. Pico Blvd. 
The public may attend. 
</P>
<P>
Patrick D. McGuire, chairman of the 44th Assembly District Committee, has 
announced that he is exploring the idea of running for the 44th District seat 
in 1990. McGuire says he will seek the post if Assemblyman Tom Hayden (D-Santa 
Monica) steps aside to run for state insurance commissioner. 
</P>
<P>
McGuire, 38, a real estate broker, is a veteran activist. He serves on the Los 
Angeles County Democratic Contral Committee and is a board member of Heal the 
Bay and the Ballona Lagoon Marine Preserve Inc., two environmental groups. 
</P>
