<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HQ Office Supplies Warehouse Inc., a retail office supply and equipment chain, 
has opened its first Orange County store. 
</P>
<P>
The store, at the corner of Harbor Boulevard and Imperial Highway in Fullerton, 
offers printing, engraving, facsimile and mailing services. It also sells 
business machines, furniture, software and office supplies. 
</P>
<P>
The chain's other Southern California stores are in Alhambra, Bellflower and 
Culver City. 
</P>
<P>
The Long Beach-based company announced this week that it plans to open up to 16 
stores by the end of this year. Of those, six should open within the next 3 
months, said Brad R. Tukey, company president and chief executive. 
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to establish and maintain a clearly dominant position for office 
supplies" in the region, Tukey said. 
</P>
