<P>
BRIEFCASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nolana Robbins of Tustin has been named controller at Donahue Schriber, a 
Newport Beach-based commercial real estate developer and shopping center 
manager. Donahue Schriber owns or manages 8.5 million square feet of commercial 
and mixed-use space in Southern California, including Newport Center/Fashion 
Island in Newport Beach. 
</P>
