AMWAY WOULD SELL PERFUME UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amway Corp. said today it would sell Avon Products Inc.'s prestige fragrance 
business if its attempt to buy Avon for more than $2 billion succeeds. 
</P>
<P>
The business includes such higher-priced perfumes as Giorgio Beverly Hills, 
Oscar de la Renta, Cher, Valentino, Perry Ellis and Deneuve, which are sold in 
stores instead of by Avon's person-to-person sales force. 
</P>
<P>
Avon said the business is expected to run up sales of more than $300 million 
this year. Spokesman John Cox said the company had no comment on Amway's stated 
plan, which was in a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. 
