<P>
KENTUCKY DERBY JOCKEY SUSPENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LOUISVILLE, Ky. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Churchill Downs stewards announced a five-day suspension today for jockey 
Clarence (Jo Jo) Ladner III for careless riding in the Kentucky Derby last 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The suspension begins Friday and continues through Wednesday but excludes 
Monday, the stewards said. 
</P>
<P>
They did not elaborate on the careless riding. Ladner was aboard Northern Wolf, 
which finished sixth in the race won by Sunday Silence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
